item.title: 【Helpdesk】How can I change the Complexity Index of a E-AC3 JOC (Dolby Digital Plus with Dolby Atmos) file
item.description: Trying to play some Dolby Atmos rips on iPhone and noticed it detected some as “Multichannel” while some are “Dolby Atmos.” At first I thought it was the Codec ID, but looking into it, some rips, mainly from Amazon Music, have the Complexity Index as “Not Present/16.” The files that are detected as Dolby Atmos on iPhone don’t say “Not Present.” Is there a way you can use ffmpeg or MP4Box to remove the “Not Present” from the Complexity Index? I think this could help me and other uploaders with their Dolby Atmos rips to allow for greater compatibility with other devices.
